Thanks for the feedback! If your issue is related to the Flutter framework itself,
please open an issue at
[github.com/flutter/flutter](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/new).

## Steps to Reproduce

When I use Android studio or intellij to create flutter project,
When opening lib/main.dart for editing, in class _MyHomePageState extends State<MyHomePage>, you can normally use the code completion function to re-parent the method, such as initState(),
But when I open the directory for Android at the moment app/src/main/kotlin/com/example/my_flutter/MainActivity.kt
The development tool has a loading process. After that, when you go back to main.dart to edit the code, you cannot use the code completion function to overload the parent class method initState().
Also, many code completion functions do not work properly. I tried recreating the project, and reinstalling the development tools did not restore this code completion unless I reinstalled Windows.
This question has been bothering me for a long time, and I hope to get your reply. thanks

comment_data.body: Thanks for including the version info. This problem was fixed in Flutter stable 3.0.2, from June 10. It may not have rolled into beta yet, or perhaps your beta is out of date.

title: Code auto-completion is abnormal
